  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Trim, then finely slice your<strong> spring onion</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623079262516-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623079262516-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623079262516-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623079262516-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1623079262516-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>lean</strong> <strong>beef mince</strong> to a large mixing bowl with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, 1/3 of the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> (save the rest for later!) and mix it all up (clean hands are the best way!), then divide the <strong>meatball mixture</strong> into 3 meatballs per person</p><p>Add the<strong> lean beef meatballs </strong>to a lightly oiled baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623079271628-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623079271628-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623079271628-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623079271628-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1623079271628-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the lean beef meatballs are in the oven, rinse your<strong> white long grain rice</strong> until the water runs clear, then add it to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623079278277-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623079278277-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623079278277-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623079278277-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1623079278277-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, slice 1/4 of your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> thinly so that you are left with chilli rounds (save these for garnish!)</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Top, tail and peel your <strong>carrot[s]</strong>, then continue to peel lengths until you end up with a pile of carrot ribbons</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623079284005-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623079284005-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623079284005-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623079284005-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1623079284005-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>In a small bowl combine your<strong> hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a small splash of <strong>water</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> and stir to combine – this is your <strong>spiced hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623079291143-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623079291143-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623079291143-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623079291143-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1623079291143-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>spinach</strong> and cook for 1 min or until beginning to wilt</p><p>Once wilted, remove the pan from the heat and add your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> carrot ribbons </strong>and <strong>remaining sliced spring onion </strong>to the pan – this is your <strong>sesame veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1623079297123-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1623079297123-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1623079297123-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1623079297123-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1623079297123-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the<strong> sesame</strong> <strong>veg</strong> to a plate and cover to keep warm</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat</p><p>Remove the <strong>cooked lean beef meatballs</strong> from the oven and add them to the pan with the<strong> spiced hoisin sauce</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min, coating the meatballs in the sauce until thickened and becoming sticky – these are your<strong> spiced hoisin lean beef meatballs</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1623079303569-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1623079303569-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1623079303569-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1623079303569-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1623079303569-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>hoisin lean beef meatballs</strong> with the <strong>sesame veg</strong> and <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Spoon over the <strong>spiced hoisin sauce</strong> from the pan and garnish with the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong> and <strong>chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
